A note on this piece in particular: the "Classic" color palette will always hold a special place in my heart - it was the first and only color scheme I was using when I first developed this algorithm 3-4 years ago. Plus the black and white is just so minimal and elegant

Highly encourage people to go back and revisit their Atlanta pieces - really reminded me why I was so proud of making them in the first place. 

They end up being much more than just shapes moving around a screen - but only if you allow yourself to immerse

When Atlanta was released, I put out a disclaimer to "view each piece for at least 45 seconds to allow deeper, more satisfying patterns to emerge"

I hadn't followed that advice in a while, but I recently stumbled on this piece and really allowed myself to get mesmerized... wow
